com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.types

Class RootSyntaxAST

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.AbstractSyntaxAST
      • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.types.RootSyntaxAST

  • public class RootSyntaxAST
extends AbstractSyntaxAST
    Used if you want to create a new RootSyntaxAST. It doesn't has an AbstractParser because you shouldn't treat this class like that. There should only be one instance for one ArkoiClass.

    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public RootSyntaxAST parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                              SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        Parses a new TypeSyntaxAST with the given parameters, where the SyntaxAnalyzer is used to check the syntax and the parent AbstractSyntaxAST is used to see if this AST can be created inside the parent. It will parse every ImportDefinitionSyntaxAST, VariableDefinitionSyntaxAST and FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST which are present at the root-level (the first layer of the AST). Besides that it will parse also AnnotationSyntaxASTs but they return a followed FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST or VariableDefinitionSyntaxAST. So basically just these three types of ASTs are getting parsed.
        Specified by:
        parseAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the parent AbstractSyntaxAST which should get used to check if the AbstractSyntaxAST can be created inside it.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used for checking the syntax with methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) )} or SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesNextToken(SymbolToken.SymbolType).
        Returns:
        null if an error occurred or the RootSyntaxAST if everything worked correctly.

      • printSyntaxAST

        public void printSyntaxAST(java.io.PrintStream printStream,
                           java.lang.String indents)
        Prints out a Tree for the RootSyntaxAST class. It will show every ImportDefinitionSyntaxAST, VariableDefinitionSyntaxAST and FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST. This method should just been called by ArkoiCompiler.printSyntaxTree(PrintStream).
        Specified by:
        printSyntaxAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        printStream - the PrintStream which should get used for the output.
        indents - the indents which the Tree should add before printing a new line.
